	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The Dynavision uses the same connector as the Mega Drive, the Master System and the Atari, those are easy to find, so there is no need to destry the gun. But in order to have it fit the NES, I'd have to cut the wire of a NES controller for it's connector, and that's what I don't want to do.
<br />
<br />I guess I could also install a MD/SMS/Atari connector to the NES controller so that it could still be used with it's former connector that became an adapter.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


