	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>tepples</b> [ Sat Aug 01, 2009 8:41 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />A standard light gun contains a focusing lens, a 1-pixel photosensor tuned to the phosphors of a color CRT, and a trigger button. Stock Zapper light guns also have a spring mechanism to simulate the pull weight of a double-action pistol's trigger. Some players open the Zapper and disconnect the spring for less noise and less strain on the trigger finger; I guess this would simulate a pre-set trigger like that of a Glock pistol.
<br />
<br />The Wii Zapper that comes with <em>Link's Crossbow Training</em> holds a Wii Remote, which in turn has a 128x96 pixel camera and an accelerometer.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


